        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued June 24 at 3:16PM EDT by NWS Northern Indiana</headline>
        <description>At 316 PM EDT, Doppler radar was tracking strong thunderstorms along
a line extending from near Homer to near Centreville. Movement was
east at 20 mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 40 mph and pea size hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor hail damage to vegetation is
possible.

Locations impacted include...
Three Rivers, Union City, Centreville, Colon, Nottawa, Girard,
Leonidas, Mendon, Sherwood, Fairfax, Wasepi, Findley, and Hodunk.

This includes Interstate 69 in Michigan between mile markers 20 and
21.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.</instruction>
